00:20:49,039 --> 00:20:50,215
Thank you, Squad Leader.

264
00:20:50,215 --> 00:20:52,355
- Let's go. 
 - Hurry up.

265
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:55,339
Bye, Vice-Captain.

266
00:21:02,229 --> 00:21:02,954
Is this okay?

267
00:21:02,954 --> 00:21:04,754
It's okay.

268
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,039
Oh my God.

269
00:21:21,039 --> 00:21:24,218
It's so late, why isn't he back yet? His stamina is really bad.

270
00:21:24,218 --> 00:21:26,220
It's getting dark.

271
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:27,769
Stop waiting.

272
00:21:27,769 --> 00:21:29,089
- Captain. 
 - Captain.

273
00:21:29,089 --> 00:21:31,329
- Call him. 
 - Okay.

274
00:21:35,301 --> 00:21:37,763
The call got through. No one answered.

275
00:21:37,763 --> 00:21:39,600
Take the car. Bring him back.

276
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:41,100
Okay.

277
00:21:56,817 --> 00:21:58,693
Captain.

278
00:21:58,693 --> 00:21:59,820
- Yang Chi. 
 - Yes, Sir.

279
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:02,055
No need to go.

280
00:22:02,055 --> 00:22:03,555
He's back.

281
00:22:47,467 --> 00:22:48,602
- Jiang Yi. 
 - Yes, Sir.

282
00:22:48,602 --> 00:22:51,042
- Take good care of the instructor. 
 - Yes, Sir.

283
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:55,175
You've worked hard, Instructor.

284
00:23:01,580 --> 00:23:04,621
Instructor, have a sip of warm water.

285
00:23:10,624 --> 00:23:12,951
Instructor, take it easy.

286
00:23:23,127 --> 00:23:27,359
The previous instructor must be excellent, right?

287
00:23:27,359 --> 00:23:29,743
I've heard about him.

288
00:23:29,743 --> 00:23:33,143
Yes, Brother Jun is very nice.

289
00:23:34,381 --> 00:23:35,881
Do you all

290
00:23:38,015 --> 00:23:40,420
hate me?

291
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:42,020
Not really.

292
00:23:42,799 --> 00:23:44,324
How should I put it?

293
00:23:44,324 --> 00:23:47,976
Instructor, let me tell you the truth, don't get angry.

294
00:23:48,873 --> 00:23:52,383
Do you feel like you're part of our team?

295
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:55,357
I think

296
00:23:56,537 --> 00:23:59,096
Song Yan and I have disagreements.

297
00:23:59,096 --> 00:24:00,841
"Disagreements"?

298
00:24:00,841 --> 00:24:02,279
What do you mean?

299
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:07,359
He's too rigid and too harsh.

300
00:24:07,359 --> 00:24:10,440
Instructor, you have to think the other way around.

301
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:12,419
He can't be lenient.

302
00:24:12,419 --> 00:24:14,879
The value of life is above everything else.

303
00:24:15,722 --> 00:24:19,459
Captain is highly sentimental.

304
00:24:19,459 --> 00:24:21,699
But he doesn't express it.

305
00:24:21,699 --> 00:24:23,359
As for his strictness,

306
00:24:23,359 --> 00:24:24,920
it's definitely for discipline.

307
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:27,680
This fire station is like being at war.

308
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:30,060
Discipline is above all else.

309
00:24:30,971 --> 00:24:32,911
What was

310
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,406
the former instructor like?

311
00:24:37,063 --> 00:24:38,904
In the past,

312
00:24:39,559 --> 00:24:42,781
one emphasized discipline, the other one valued emotions.

313
00:25:29,262 --> 00:25:31,062
Instructor!

314
00:25:42,997 --> 00:25:46,301
   

315
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:57,684
 It's now 10:13 p.m. 

316
00:26:57,684 --> 00:27:00,643
 The temperature is 30.3 degrees Celsius (~86.5 F). 

317
00:27:01,930 --> 00:27:03,430
Thank you.

318
00:27:46,502 --> 00:27:49,243
Mom, what brings you here?

319
00:27:50,671 --> 00:27:52,809
It's been a long time since I've been here.

320
00:27:52,809 --> 00:27:57,426
I happened to pass by today. So I came up to take a look.

321
00:28:02,716 --> 00:28:04,744
It's pretty good.

322
00:28:04,744 --> 00:28:06,745
It's pretty clean.

323
00:28:11,447 --> 00:28:14,668
I bought dinner for you.

324
00:28:15,629 --> 00:28:17,464
I'm leaving.

325
00:28:17,464 --> 00:28:18,864
Mom.

326
00:28:21,101 --> 00:28:25,700
Were you thinking that there is another person at home?

327
00:28:28,575 --> 00:28:30,015
No.

328
00:28:30,015 --> 00:28:32,190
You won't do

329
00:28:33,735 --> 00:28:36,600
anything that would make me sad.

330
00:28:39,553 --> 00:28:42,841
You're right. I won't.

331
00:28:43,416 --> 00:28:47,376
I've been thinking these past few days.

332
00:28:48,687 --> 00:28:52,735
Can I stop being like this from now on?

333
00:28:52,735 --> 00:28:54,626
Can I

334
00:28:55,676 --> 00:28:58,056
be bold for once?

335
00:29:01,575 --> 00:29:07,579
When your brother paid a fine to the bank, I knew something was off.

336
00:29:09,057 --> 00:29:11,885
Is it that guy with the last name, Song?

337
00:29:11,885 --> 00:29:14,160
The parents behave improperly, and their son follows suit.

338
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:17,526
Not a single person in that family has good character.

339
00:29:17,526 --> 00:29:19,133
Mom.

340
00:29:20,119 --> 00:29:23,059
You don't have to attack him like that.

341
00:29:23,063 --> 00:29:25,163
Right now,

342
00:29:26,079 --> 00:29:28,183
I have nothing to do with him.

343
00:29:28,183 --> 00:29:30,964
Do you want to have something to do with him?

344
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:35,976
If that's the case, then you should go abroad.

345
00:29:35,976 --> 00:29:37,580
Mom,

346
00:29:37,580 --> 00:29:39,888
I feel very sad.

347
00:29:39,888 --> 00:29:42,304
You know what?

348
00:29:42,304 --> 00:29:44,184
He came to my house a few days ago.

349
00:29:44,184 --> 00:29:46,060
He was there.

350
00:29:46,060 --> 00:29:48,079
He made porridge for me.

351
00:29:48,079 --> 00:29:50,359
I've been living here alone for such a long time.

352
00:29:50,359 --> 00:29:53,720
It was the first time I felt at home.

353
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:58,319
But that feeling quickly disappeared

354
00:29:58,319 --> 00:29:59,969
when he left.

355
00:29:59,969 --> 00:30:01,520
I really wanted to ask him to stay.

356
00:30:01,520 --> 00:30:03,303
But I didn't dare to do so.

357
00:30:03,303 --> 00:30:07,508
Because you were afraid that I'd be upset. So you want to convince me first.

358
00:30:07,508 --> 00:30:08,633
Mom...

359
00:30:08,633 --> 00:30:11,513
You should dispel this thought as soon as possible.

360
00:30:11,513 --> 00:30:17,047
I already told you. Don't go against your parents for an outsider.

361
00:30:17,047 --> 00:30:19,808
He doesn't have to be an outsider.

362
00:30:21,447 --> 00:30:23,816
Just a bowl of porridge?

363
00:30:23,816 --> 00:30:27,849
It was just a bowl of porridge, and you can't stop thinking about it.

364
00:30:27,849 --> 00:30:30,909
Your dad was worried you'd work too hard.

365
00:30:30,909 --> 00:30:33,633
He bought an apartment near the hospital for you.

366
00:30:33,633 --> 00:30:34,833
He bought you a car.

367
00:30:34,833 --> 00:30:37,337
And the best hospital,

368
00:30:37,337 --> 00:30:39,936
including the best team of physicians to guide you.

369
00:30:39,936 --> 00:30:45,009
I joined this hospital based on my own abilities.

370
00:30:46,272 --> 00:30:48,215
Don't be silly, Kid.

371
00:30:48,215 --> 00:30:50,056
That's because your last name is Meng.

372
00:30:50,056 --> 00:30:52,368
You don't have to know about the ways of the world.

373
00:30:52,368 --> 00:30:55,007
You don't have to please Assistant Director Liu.

374
00:30:55,007 --> 00:30:57,484
You can do whatever you want.

375
00:30:57,484 --> 00:31:00,321
It's because your family has got your back.

376
00:31:00,321 --> 00:31:02,025
Look at your dad and brother.

377
00:31:02,025 --> 00:31:06,079
For the sake of this family, they are facing all kinds of pressures every day.

378
00:31:06,079 --> 00:31:08,268
They work hard.

379
00:31:08,268 --> 00:31:09,968
But you?

380
00:31:11,119 --> 00:31:13,639
For this little bit of affection,

381
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:18,712
a bowl of porridge, you act as if you're on the verge of dying.

382
00:31:18,712 --> 00:31:21,592
You forget the gratitude toward your parents.

383
00:31:21,592 --> 00:31:25,018
I remember it. Of course, I remember it, Mom.

384
00:31:25,018 --> 00:31:27,621
That's why I've been restraining myself.

385
00:31:27,621 --> 00:31:31,647
I've been in pain. I don't want to make you sad.

386
00:31:35,929 --> 00:31:37,529
Qin Qin.

387
00:31:39,299 --> 00:31:42,359
I don't ask for anything from you.

388
00:31:45,488 --> 00:31:47,703
All I want

389
00:31:47,703 --> 00:31:50,343
is that you can be an obedient child.

390
00:31:52,079 --> 00:31:55,565
Okay. Dress right, dress.

391
00:31:55,565 --> 00:31:56,983
Look forward.

392
00:31:56,983 --> 00:31:58,583
Stand at ease.

393
00:32:00,567 --> 00:32:04,926
For the new recruit assessment, you must get a good grade.

394
00:32:04,926 --> 00:32:07,380
Captain said that if you don't get good grades,

395
00:32:07,380 --> 00:32:09,663
you have to pack and leave.

396
00:32:09,663 --> 00:32:10,792
Do you have confidence?

397
00:32:10,792 --> 00:32:11,895
 Yes! 

398
00:32:11,895 --> 00:32:13,098
Will you embarrass Shili Tai?

399
00:32:13,098 --> 00:32:14,933
 Yes! 

400
00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:16,633
"Yes"?

401
00:32:17,323 --> 00:32:18,338
 No! 

402
00:32:18,338 --> 00:32:20,427
- Louder! 
  - No! 

403
00:32:20,427 --> 00:32:22,127
Set off.

404
00:32:47,294 --> 00:32:48,484
   

405
00:33:23,189 --> 00:33:25,136
   

406
00:33:25,136 --> 00:33:27,160
Even if I have a limp, we still get the highest total score.

407
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:28,642
Tell me, how should we celebrate?

408
00:33:28,642 --> 00:33:30,187
- That's right! 
 - Let's celebrate.

409
00:33:30,187 --> 00:33:31,643
But it's your treat.

410
00:33:31,643 --> 00:33:33,214
- You guys are so weak. 
 - We treat you?

411
00:33:33,214 --> 00:33:34,720
You came in in first place, and we have to treat you?

412
00:33:34,720 --> 00:33:36,596
Are you kidding me?

413
00:33:37,328 --> 00:33:38,920
Slow down.

414
00:33:38,920 --> 00:33:40,160
- This way. 
 - Slow down.

415
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,887
- Come, watch out. 
 - Quick.

416
00:33:41,887 --> 00:33:43,384
Slow down.

417
00:33:43,384 --> 00:33:45,040
Okay.

418
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,392
Indeed.

419
00:33:46,392 --> 00:33:48,760
What do you think, Da Peng?

420
00:33:48,760 --> 00:33:50,931
What do you mean?

421
00:33:50,931 --> 00:33:53,369
If you don't treat us...

422
00:33:56,366 --> 00:33:57,804
Don't touch that!

423
00:33:57,804 --> 00:33:59,512
Don't take them from me!

424
00:33:59,512 --> 00:34:01,041
They're all my babies.

425
00:34:01,041 --> 00:34:02,119
Take care of your injuries.

426
00:34:02,119 --> 00:34:04,440
 All of you are taking the opportunity to steal my things. 

427
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:06,240
 Do you know how expensive they are? 

428
00:34:06,240 --> 00:34:08,039
 They're all my babies. 

429
00:34:08,039 --> 00:34:10,679
You've snatched them all. You guys are over the line.

430
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:11,979
What's wrong?

431
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:16,937
- Instructor... 
  - Hello, Instructor. 

432
00:34:16,937 --> 00:34:19,119
Instructor, I'm left with an empty box.

433
00:34:19,119 --> 00:34:20,311
They've snatched them all.

434
00:34:20,311 --> 00:34:23,197
Da Peng, how's your leg?

435
00:34:23,197 --> 00:34:26,034
I applied some medicine to it. It's much better now.

436
00:34:27,314 --> 00:34:29,373
Take it easy.

437
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:34,226
Instructor, we didn't embarrass Captain today, right?

438
00:34:34,226 --> 00:34:35,490
Of course not.

439
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:36,855
You guys performed very well.

440
00:34:36,855 --> 00:34:39,719
I think he's happy. He's elated secretly.

441
00:34:41,079 --> 00:34:43,952
Can you take this opportunity

442
00:34:43,952 --> 00:34:47,480
to ask Captain to let us go to the fire scene sooner?

443
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:49,987
 - Yes. 
 - Yes, Instructor. 

444
00:34:49,987 --> 00:34:53,263
No way. We have to follow the rules and regulations.

445
00:34:53,263 --> 00:34:54,840
You've been waiting for so long. Just wait a little longer.

446
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,345
It's almost there.

447
00:34:56,345 --> 00:34:58,079
These regulations are unreasonable.

448
00:34:58,079 --> 00:35:00,105
That's right. We're so capable now.

449
00:35:00,105 --> 00:35:02,236
Why don't you talk to him yourselves?

450
00:35:02,236 --> 00:35:04,927
Forget it. I'm afraid of being scolded.

451
00:35:04,927 --> 00:35:07,280
Is he that scary?

452
00:35:07,280 --> 00:35:09,309
 Yes! 

453
00:35:09,309 --> 00:35:11,578
- Song Yan. 
 - It's not negotiable.

454
00:35:11,578 --> 00:35:15,659
I think the performance of the new recruits in the assessment is really outstanding.

455
00:35:16,777 --> 00:35:19,555
Some fire missions can be handed over to them.

456
00:35:19,555 --> 00:35:22,360
It can also accelerate the transition between the new and old members of the fire station.

457
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:24,780
A fire scene is not an amusement park.

458
00:35:24,780 --> 00:35:27,526
Passing the assessment only shows that their technical skills meet the standard.

459
00:35:27,526 --> 00:35:32,059
Their ability to respond on the spot, psychological resilience and mental willpower

460
00:35:32,059 --> 00:35:33,160
still need to be trained.

461
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:37,471
That's why they need practical experience and missions to accelerate their growth.

462
00:35:37,471 --> 00:35:41,519
Once you've learned the word "sacrifice," come to me to ask for another chance.

463
00:35:41,519 --> 00:35:44,145
Sometimes a sacrifice is avoidable.

464
00:35:44,145 --> 00:35:46,679
Under current technological conditions,

465
00:35:46,679 --> 00:35:49,781
the safety factor has greatly improved.

466
00:35:49,781 --> 00:35:52,294
In the fire at a high-rise apartment in Dongjiang,

467
00:35:52,294 --> 00:35:53,395
there were two casualties.

468
00:35:54,285 --> 00:35:58,425
The chemical plant explosion at Liaoning, four casualties.

469
00:35:58,425 --> 00:36:02,533
The fire at Mountain 625 at Shannan, 17 casualties.

470
00:36:03,193 --> 00:36:05,792
Their average age is less than 22 years old.

471
00:36:09,777 --> 00:36:11,957
Sacrifice is indeed not a tradition,

472
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:15,359
but it's the reality this team

473
00:36:15,359 --> 00:36:17,680
has to face.

474
00:36:26,518 --> 00:36:28,762
I actually don't understand.

475
00:36:28,762 --> 00:36:31,409
With your family background,

476
00:36:31,409 --> 00:36:33,126
you can get opportunities anywhere.

477
00:36:33,126 --> 00:36:35,495
Why do you have to come here to create trouble?

478
00:36:35,495 --> 00:36:37,608
What's that supposed to mean?

479
00:36:38,865 --> 00:36:41,666
Do you think I'm here to enhance my resume?

480
00:36:41,666 --> 00:36:43,719
What's wrong with my family background?

481
00:36:43,719 --> 00:36:46,740
Captain Song, I think this is reverse discrimination.

482
00:36:46,740 --> 00:36:48,000
Can't I love this profession?

483
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:51,200
I like this profession. I want to do something for this profession, can't I?

484
00:36:53,113 --> 00:36:54,366
Yes, I know.

485
00:36:54,366 --> 00:36:56,389
It's hard for you to accept me emotionally.

486
00:36:56,389 --> 00:36:59,369
I'm here to take over from Instructor Suo.

487
00:36:59,369 --> 00:37:03,824
There are many things that I can't empathize with you like he did,

488
00:37:03,824 --> 00:37:05,491
or have a tacit understanding with you.

489
00:37:06,693 --> 00:37:09,272
But we can develop that over time.

490
00:37:10,753 --> 00:37:12,933
I just want you to know one thing.

491
00:37:12,933 --> 00:37:14,533
I'm

492
00:37:15,882 --> 00:37:17,922
not here to fool around.

493
00:37:40,791 --> 00:37:43,608
   

494
00:37:50,024 --> 00:37:52,485
Are you still selling cosmetics?

495
00:37:53,729 --> 00:37:55,593
These are small, cheap brands.

496
00:37:55,593 --> 00:37:56,809
These are authentic products.

497
00:37:56,809 --> 00:37:59,713
I've been fined so much money, I need to make up for it.

498
00:37:59,713 --> 00:38:03,209
Right, do you know any quick ways to make money?

499
00:38:03,209 --> 00:38:06,185
I really need to earn money now.

500
00:38:06,885 --> 00:38:09,856
When I find a way to make money, we can make money together.

501
00:38:09,856 --> 00:38:11,091
Thanks, Sister.

502
00:38:11,091 --> 00:38:13,358
Do you need money that badly?

503
00:38:13,358 --> 00:38:16,327
We're graduating soon, and I feel anxious.

504
00:38:16,327 --> 00:38:18,963
Besides, our major is very niche.

505
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:20,798
The wages are low.

506
00:38:20,798 --> 00:38:23,570
I'm not a local like you guys.

507
00:38:23,570 --> 00:38:28,029
If I want to stay here after graduation, I won't even be able to afford the rent.

508
00:38:29,648 --> 00:38:32,329
Find a rich boyfriend then.

509
00:38:32,329 --> 00:38:33,553
You know what?

510
00:38:33,553 --> 00:38:37,856
Wu Qing Qing in the next dormitory found one.

511
00:38:37,856 --> 00:38:39,971
That kind of guy.

512
00:38:39,971 --> 00:38:41,321
No wonder.

513
00:38:41,321 --> 00:38:43,790
The last time I saw her, she was carrying a Chanel bag.

514
00:38:43,790 --> 00:38:45,507
I thought it was fake.

515
00:38:45,507 --> 00:38:46,753
It's authentic.

516
00:38:46,753 --> 00:38:48,641
Doesn't she feel unethical about it?

517
00:38:48,641 --> 00:38:50,625
Who knows?

518
00:38:50,625 --> 00:38:53,192
Girls, can we have some ambition?

519
00:38:53,192 --> 00:38:55,736
When it comes to making money, we should rely on ourselves.

520
00:38:55,736 --> 00:38:57,665
Relying on a boyfriend is useless.

521
00:38:57,665 --> 00:38:59,070
Just wait and see.

522
00:38:59,070 --> 00:39:03,498
I, Zhai Miao, will definitely become a boss through my own efforts.

523
00:39:03,498 --> 00:39:05,574
Boss, I wish you success soon.

524
00:39:05,574 --> 00:39:06,639
Okay.

525
00:39:06,639 --> 00:39:08,043
I'll hold hands with the boss.

526
00:39:08,043 --> 00:39:09,543
Come.

527
00:39:10,202 --> 00:39:11,289
You can hold this hand.

528
00:39:11,289 --> 00:39:13,590
Thank you, Boss.

529
00:39:59,086 --> 00:40:00,913
Ye Zi.

530
00:40:01,896 --> 00:40:04,023
This is your campus card, right?

531
00:40:04,737 --> 00:40:06,504
- So you picked it up. 
  - No.

